review_blob: A deep golden color, malty aroma with herbal and alcohol undertones, the herbal and alcohol elements play a role in the flavor. A solid golden ale all around, refreshing if you are having 3 or less.

The aroma is remniscent of American floral hops, but probably comes from light malt and high fermenting temperatures, producing esters and phenols. The initial taste is surprisingly smooth with an apple cidery flavor that is not unpleasant.
A better than average amber ale with sour and sweet (crystal 40 barley?) mingling on the tongue before a slightly bitter finish. A solid effort from an interesting microbryggeri.
